title: ISic001195. I.Sicily inscription 001195
body:
Facsimile Images

Ἀρτεμιδ[---]
Ψυ̣χ̣ [---]

Apparatus criticus

Text according to Kaibel in IG ; Kaibel suggests: Ἀρτεμιδ[ώ]ρο[υ]

translation

commentary

The fragment was reported first in the second edition of Gualtherus' corpus, where it was transcribed in Latin letters. As a result, it was included also by Mommsen in CIL (no.7466) and the doublet does not seem to have been noticed by either Mommsen or Kaibel.
